Anachronistic Folly of Grand National Party Assailed 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, September 29 (KCNA) -- A spokesman for the National Democratic�@Front of south Korea (NDFSK) issued a statement on September 25 denouncing�@the Grand National Party for its vicious moves to drive the National�@Assembly into shambles, according to Kuguk Joson Internet site.
 The statement said: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The regular session of the National Assembly that opened on September 1 is�@causing serious disappointment and resentment of the people as it is wasting�@time in never-ceasing political disputes, failing to discuss a proper law�@for reform. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 We can hardly repress bitter anger at the fact that the GNP, which suffered�@a miserable defeat in the general election, is trying to turn the NA into a�@theater of rowdyism by throwing a snag in the way of every legislative�@overture badly needed for political reform and the development of�@inter-Korean relations. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The NDFSK sternly denounces such vicious moves of the GNP to drive the NA�@to a catastrophic phase as an unpardonable criminal act intended to revive�@the past rotten NA, plant-like NA stained with pro-U.S. flunkeyism, fascist�@dictatorship, corruption and anti-north confrontation. The 17th-term NA�@should be one for a progressive reform to entomb what is old, a�@reunification-oriented NA contributing to the development of inter-Korean�@relations. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The forces for progressive reform in the NA should frustrate the�@treacherous maneuvers of the conservative forces to meet the aspiration and�@demand of the people and daringly conduct supra-partisan legislative�@activities helpful to the new policy and the development of inter-Korean�@relations. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Those bent on turning the NA into a scene of fight for the interests and�@stratagem of a party are a handful of diehard pro-U.S. conservatives and�@their anachronistic folly can not evade a stern judgment by history.�@&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The NDFSK, jointly with the people of all strata desirous of progressive�@policy and independent reunification, will invigorate the struggle to�@resolutely smash the last-ditch moves of the pro-U.S. conservative forces�@swimming against the will of the people and the trend of the times and bring�@earlier a new policy for independence and democracy, a new land of�@reunification desired by the whole Korean nation, free from outside forces�@and traitors.

Sojourn of Delegation of Russian Supreme Court in Pyongyang 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, September 29 (KCNA) -- The talks between the delegations of the�@DPRK Central Court and the Supreme Court of the Russian Federation were held�@at the Mansudae Assembly Hall on Tuesday.
 Both sides exchanged views on cooperation between the courts and a series�@of issues of mutual concern at the talks. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Present at the talks from the DPRK side were members of the delegation of�@the Central Court led by its Chief Justice Kim Pyong Ryul and from the�@Russian side members of the delegation of the Supreme Court headed by its�@President Byacheslav Mikhailovich Rebezev and Ambassador Andrei�@Gennadiyevich Karlov and staff members of the Russian embassy here. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 That day the delegation of the Supreme Court of the Russian Federation laid�@a wreath before the Liberation Tower. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The delegation arrived in Pyongyang on Tuesday.

S. Korean Military's Move to Dispatch Special Warfare Troops to�@Iraq under Fire 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, September 29 (KCNA) -- A spokesman for the Committee for the�@Peaceful Reunification of the Fatherland issued a statement on Sept. 28 to�@denounce the south Korean military for openly talking about the dispatch of�@special warfare troops to Iraq aimed to let them accumulate experience in�@civil operation.
 The south Korean military does not hide the fact that its troops dispatched�@to East Timor, Afghanistan, Iraq, etc. are getting ready to conduct civil�@operations in the north in case of emergency under the special warfare�@command, the statement said, and continued: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It is the first time that the military disclosed that the dispatch of its�@troops to Iraq is aimed to accumulate experience in civil operation, hinting�@at their future operations in the north. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 This clearly proves that its dispatch of special warfare troops to Iraq is�@prompted by its sinister and provocative design against the DPRK, not to�@protect its units already dispatched there. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The committee vehemently denounces in the name of all Koreans desirous of�@peace and reunification of the country the south Korean military's moves�@against the north as an outright challenge to the June 15 North-South Joint�@Declaration under which the north and the south committed themselves to�@achieve reconciliation, unity and reunification through national cooperation�@in the idea of "By our nation itself" and as an intolerable and dangerous�@provocation. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It is a pipedream for the south Korean military to conduct civil operation�@on the Korean peninsula. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The south Korean authorities had better ponder over the grave consequences�@to be entailed by their anti-national civil operations, immediately stop the�@criminal additional troop dispatch to Iraq and withdraw troops already sent�@to Iraq at the earliest possible date to prevent the recurrence of such�@terrible disaster as the case of Kim Son Il. The north will force them to�@pay a high price for their criminal moves to escalate the confrontation with�@it.

U.S. Plan for Preemptive Attack on DPRK under Fire 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, September 29 (KCNA) -- The United States is making desperate�@efforts to bring down the dignified socialist system in the DPRK by use of�@double-dealing tactics of dialogue and military option. But this is a�@pipe-dream. Minju Joson Wednesday says this in a signed commentary.
 It goes on: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The U.S. is paying lip-service to dialogue and peaceful settlement. It is,�@in actuality, dealing with the nuclear issue with main emphasis laid on the�@military solution to the issue. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Rice, assistant to the U.S. president for national security, recently�@blustered that the U.S. has the right to use military force against north�@Korea over its nuclear issue. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Her outpouring has a thread of connection with the remark made by a�@spokesman for the Department of State that all options including the use of�@force are on the table when answering a reporter's question as to whether�@the U.S. rules out the use of force against north Korea. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 This suffices to clearly prove that the preemptive military attack on the�@DPRK is an official stand of the U.S. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It is the true intention of the U.S. to use the nuclear issue as a pretext�@and justification to mount a preemptive military attack on the DPRK. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The DPRK will never abandon its principle, yielding to the U.S. going�@reckless, bereft of reason.

Japan Hit for Provocative Act against Pyongyang Declaration 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, September 29 (KCNA) -- It has recently been disclosed that the General Staff of the Ground Force of the Japan Defense Agency is working out "a plan for combating terrorism" including a drastic arms buildup of the Ground "Self-Defense Force" under the pretext of coping with "large-scale terrorism" of the DPRK.
 Commenting on this, a Rodong Sinmun analyst Wednesday   says: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Japanese reactionaries are drawing up the "plan for combating terrorism" and seeking a drastic arms buildup by pulling up the DPRK over its fictitious "terrorism". This shows they are going to extremes in their moves to stage a comeback to Korea and impede the implementation of the DPRK-Japan Pyongyang Declaration. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 They have so far resorted to hectic moves to turn Japan into a military power and launch into overseas expansion on the plea of the non-existent "missile threat" and "nuclear threat" of the DPRK by zealously banking on the U.S. hostile policy toward the DPRK. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 In trying to attach the tag of "terrorism" to the DPRK, the Japan Defense Agency is pursuing a very sinister and dangerous aim to justify its scheme to stage a comeback to Korea and attain ground for turning Japan into a military power and go over to overseas expansion by joining the United States in branding the DPRK as a "criminal of terrorism". The talk of the Japanese reactionaries about the DPRK's "large-scale terrorism against Japan" is a total fiction and a malicious insult and challenge to the DPRK. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Despicable and shameless are the Japanese reactionaries who have invented the fiction of "terrorist threat" of the DPRK which has nothing to do with terrorism and, under this pretext, seek to attain their dishonest aim. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The outcries of the Japan Defense Agency over "large-scale terrorism" and its working out of the "plan for combating terrorism" are a grave provocation contradictory to the basic spirit of the Pyongyang declaration. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Japanese reactionaries should discontinue the foolish acts of obstructing the implementation of the Pyongyang declaration and bedeviling the DPRK-Japan relations, ignoring the demand of the public sentiments at home and abroad.

Strengthened Party Leadership System Called for 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, September 29 (KCNA) -- It is necessary to steadily deepen the�@work for establishing a leadership system of the Workers' Party of Korea.
This provides a sure guarantee for accomplishing the revolutionary cause of�@Juche started by President Kim Il Sung by achieving a final victory in the�@anti-imperialist and anti-U.S. confrontation and bringing about�@uninterrupted leaping advances in the building of a great prosperous�@powerful nation holding aloft the banner of Songun under the Party�@leadership. Rodong Sinmun Wednesday says this in a signed article. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Party is a political organization to realize the idea and leadership of�@the headquarters of the revolution and its idea and intentions are�@materialized by the Party, the article notes, and goes on: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Establishing the leadership system of the Party means building a leadership�@system of the headquarters of the revolution. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
In establishing this system nothing is more important than thoroughly�@ensuring the security and authority of the headquarters of the revolution�@and upholding its idea and leadership exploits. It is necessary to establish�@a steel-strong discipline and order whereby to deal with all matters from�@the viewpoint and stand of devotedly defending the headquarters of the�@revolution and act as one true to the idea and intention of the headquarters�@throughout the Party, the army and society. This provides a sure guarantee�@for defending the Korean revolution and socialism and achieving a final�@victory in the confrontation with the U.S. imperialists. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 In the present era of Songun, the People's Army is a core force and model�@in upholding the idea and leadership of the Party. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The DPRK can decisively smash enemies' reckless war moves and vicious plots�@to destabilize its society and win one victory after another in the�@anti-U.S. confrontation only when there are a revolutionary discipline and�@order in the whole Party and society whereby everyone loyally upholds the�@idea and leadership of the Party as required by the era of Songun just as�@the People's Army does. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 All the Party organs and officials should thoroughly establish the�@leadership system of the WPK, as required by the era of Songun, to achieve a�@decisive victory in the present anti-imperialist, anti-U.S. confrontation�@and translate the plan of leader Kim Jong Il to build a great prosperous�@powerful nation into reality as early as possible, the article�@concludes.

Koreans Called Upon to Build Structure of Their Confrontation with�@U.S. 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, September 29 (KCNA) -- It is an urgent requirement of the reality to build the structure of the Korean nation's confrontation with the U.S. in practice, says Rodong Sinmun Wednesday in a signed article.
 The United States is stepping up the preparations for preempt a military attack on the DPRK after making it an established fact under the pretext of the nuclear issue, the article says, calling on the Korean nation to build the structure of its confrontation with the U.S. in practice in order to preserve peace on this land and reunify the country now that the U.S. imperialist's military provocation moves are getting ever more pronounced as the days go by. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The article goes on: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 To this end, it is necessary for the north and the south to get united and cooperate with each other to foil the U.S. attempt to launch a new war of aggression. They should fulfill their responsibility and role in the struggle to protect the destiny of the nation as they are responsible for the peace, security and reunification of the Korean peninsula and wage a coordinated struggle against the U.S. and war. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It is also necessary to take a fixed stand and will to trust the nation and depend on its strength in this struggle. The U.S. does not wish the peace and reunification of Korea. So it does not care whether the Korean nation remains divided for an indefinite period or whether the peninsula suffers a nuclear calamity, only seeking to meet its own interests as an aggressor. It is a daydream to harbor any illusion about the U.S. or calculate that the nation can avoid the danger of war and ensure economic stability when it depends on the U.S. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Koreans in the north and the south and abroad should struggle with transparent spirit of national independence that they have to avoid the daily increasing danger of war by their concerted efforts.

Physical Strength Check-up in DPRK
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, September 29 (KCNA) -- The physical strength check-up is now in swing in the Democratic People's Republic of Korea.
 It has been conducted as an annual event in the country since Juche 37 (1948). &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The government has set August and September as physical strength examination months. The nationwide campaign is aimed to make the whole society replete with an atmosphere of making physical culture and sports mass-based and encourage the people to improve their physical fitness and prepare themselves well for labour and national defence. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 A mutual examination method has been introduced this year to boost the enthusiasm of the people. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Kim Il Sung University, the Pyongyang Maternity Hospital, institutions, industrial establishments and schools in Phyongchon District, Pyongyang, have carried on practice of all events in a planned way so that most of their members have passed the eleven-event check-up according to ages and sexes. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The physical strength examination has been dynamically conducted in all provinces, cities and counties. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The examination reflects the Korean people's optimistic spirit of making their life more beautiful with strong physical strength.

Books on Martial Arts Published in DPRK
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, September 29 (KCNA) -- Books "Stories on Celebrities of Korean Martial Arts" (Vols. 1 and 2) and "Self-defence Art of Taekwon-Do" (Vol. 1) were published in the Democratic People's Republic of Korea.
 The book "Stories on Celebrities of Korean Martial Arts" introduces 74 persons from the period of the three kingdoms (Koguryo, Paekje and Silla) to the period of the Ri Dynasty. They include famous patriotic generals who performed distinguished services in battles for defending the country and prominent masters of martial arts in different ages. It also gives a common knowledge on history and short stories on the Korean martial arts. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Given in it are episodes about Korean women who disguised themselves as men and distinguished themselves on battlefields with their wonderful martial arts. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The stories are based on the old Samguksa, Samguksagi (the history of the three kingdoms), the history of Koryo, Samgukyusa (the historic records of the three kingdoms) and the true records of the Ri Dynasty and other historic records and libraries of figures. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The book "Self-defence Art of Taekwon-Do" deals with technical skills to be applied in case of being attacked, caught and pressed on vitals and any part of body by others and in other unexpected circumstances, and the first aid methods in case of hurt. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It also introduces self-defence art for women when attacked by men. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The book gives photo-illustrated self-defence movements so that anyone can learn how to perform them by himself without other's help. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The books were authored and published by the Korean Taekwon-Do Committee and the Publishing House of Physical Culture and Sports.

Jong Ha Chol Meets CPC Friendly Visiting Group of Specialists and�@Scientists
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, September 29 (KCNA) -- Jong Ha Chol, secretary of the Central Committee of the Workers' Party of Korea, Wednesday met and had a friendly talk with the friendly visiting group of experts and scholars of the Communist Party of China led by Leng Yong, executive deputy director of the Document Research Office of the CPC Central Committee.
  On the occasion the head of the group said that during the visit to the DPRK he had an opportunity to see great achievements made by the Korean people in socialist construction. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He hoped that under the wise leadership of Kim Jong Il the people of the DPRK would achieve greater success in their struggle to build socialism of Korean style and achieve reunification of the country. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Present there were officials concerned and the Chinese ambassador e.p. to the DPRK.
